from: planner
session: wva-saturation-cycle-log label fixes

Three small changes to the logging PR (wva-log-rewrite worktree,
branch wva-saturation-cycle-log-r1). All changes are in files already
touched by the branch.

## Change 1 — Drop `cost` from per-variant log entry

In `internal/engines/saturation/engine_v2.go`, `logAnalyzerResult`:

Remove `Cost float64 \`json:"cost"\`` from the `variantEntry` struct and
remove `Cost: vc.Cost,` from the struct literal. Cost is VA-spec metadata
that belongs to a separate concern; it should not appear per-analyzer.

Result: `variants` entries become `{name, prc, label}` only.

## Change 2 — Sat_v2 capacity-store path gets label "P0-store"

In `internal/engines/analyzers/saturation_v2/analyzer.go`, `aggregateByVariant`:

When `len(replicas) == 0`, `PerReplicaCapacity` is sourced from
`a.capacityStore.Get(...)`. The current code leaves `CapacityLabel` empty
for this path. Set it to `"P0-store"` so operators can distinguish
store-derived capacity from live-observation-derived capacity.

Find the block where `len(replicas) == 0` is handled (the capacity store
fallback) and add:
```go
vc.CapacityLabel = "P0-store"
```
before appending `vc` to the result.

## Change 3 — Throughput analyzer sets CapacityLabel per tier

In `internal/engines/analyzers/throughput/analyzer.go`:

`resolveITLModel` (around line 463) has three tiers. Thread the tier label
back to where `VariantCapacity` is built in `Analyze()`. The three labels:

| Tier | Condition | Label |
|---|---|---|
| T1 | OLS fit from live observations (`observationWindow.Ready()` + `FitITLModel` succeeds) | `"T1-ols"` |
| T2 pinned | Constrained OLS with `lastFittedB` from prior fit | `"T2-pinned"` |
| T2 default | Constrained OLS with default B (cold start) | `"T2-default"` |

Read the TA code carefully to find the exact branching. The label must
reflect which path produced the `PerReplicaCapacity` value for the variant.

## After all three changes

- Update `engine_v2_log_test.go`: remove `Cost` assertions, add assertion
  that `label` field is present in variant entries.
- Update any TA tests that assert on `CapacityLabel` (or add one asserting
  the three tier labels are set correctly).
- Run all gates: `gofmt`, `make test`, `make lint`, `go build`.
- One commit covering all three changes.
- Write `plan__wva-log-label-fixes-done.md` handoff when gates are green.
  Dean will push.

## Do not
- Add cost back anywhere.
- Touch the QM analyzer (known gap, separate work).
- Change any scaling logic.
